                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/911.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Assistant Secretary of War</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">War Department</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The following cablegram was
                    received this day from the Deputy Receiver General of Dominican Customs: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Bill introduced Dominican Congress December 9 authorizes Executive to
                            contract loan of $1,500,000 specifically recognizing article 3 of the
                            treaty; 7 per <pb facs="0561" n="457" xml:id="pg_457"/> cent interest;
                            $30,000 payable monthly by General Receiver of Dominican Customs. This
                            will probably be handled by local banks. Approval of American Government
                            will not be requested until contract has been signed. In the meantime
                            Santiago Michelena advances $2,500 daily to the Government.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Shaw Oliver</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
